galoa_mul_tab(int, int) - Method in class edu.crypto2.transformations.KeyExpansion
Galois multiplication
Task:
multiply two numbers using AES (Galois) multiplication
To speed up Galois multiplication, we will use well known formula:
log(x*y)=log(x)*log(y)
x*y=antilog(log(x)*log(y))
and already calculated subresults stored in ltable and atable

getInvSBox() - Method in class edu.crypto2.data.Data
Getter for Inverse Substituton Box, for InvSubButes transformation.
Two basic components of many algorithms are substitution box ( S-Box) and permutation box ( P-Box).
AES uses SBox explicitly, while permutations are done implicitly

getTmpkey() - Method in class edu.crypto2.data.Data
tmpKey holds initial four bytes for keyExpansion.
Procedure is as follows:
1.Get last four bytes from already generated key
2.Generate new 16 bytes of key
repeat until reach full key size
